title: Celebrity Big Brother fans claim show was ‘fixed’ as they insist Coleen Nolan ‘too boring’ to win
text:
CBB FIX STORM Celebrity Big Brother fans claim show was ‘fixed’ as they insist Coleen Nolan ‘too boring’ to win 
Viewers were outraged by the result of last night's final as Coleen triumphed over Jedward By Louise Randell, Senior Showbiz Reporter 4th February 2017, 2:05 pm Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window) Comments CELEBRITY Big Brother fans have branded the show a “fix” as they claim Coleen Nolan was “too boring” to win. 
The Loose Women star was crowned champion last night, but many viewers were outraged by the result. PA:Press Association 14 Coleen Nolan has won Celebrity Big Brother 
Coleen saw off competition from Jedward in the final two and burst into tears when Emma Willis announced her name over the Irish twins. 
It came as a shock to the star as Coleen previously finished as runner-up in her previously CBB stint. 
Many fans were also shocked by the outcome as Jedward had been favourites to win. Coleen Nolan reveals she wants to save her marriage on CBB's Bit on the Side Getty Images - WireImage Jedward came second after Coleen Getty Images - WireImage Coleen was shocked and in tears at the result Coleen Nolan wins Celebrity Big Brother 2017 beating Jedward 
They flocked to Twitter to express their disappointment, insisting Coleen was not interesting enough to deserve the title. 
One wrote: "Can't believe I've sat and watched #cbb for three weeks for COLEEN NOLAN to win... biggest fix." 
Another added: "@bbuk fix so disappointing what did Coleen Nolan bring to the house nothing!!!!" 
A third tweeted: "Another celebrity big brother another fix boring Coleen Nolan did not get the most votes..." 
Coleen Nolan wins Celebrity Big Brother 2017 beating Jedward Getty Images - WireImage Coleen beat Jedward to the CBB crown PA:Press Association Coleen was in floods of tears as she came outside to greet the crowd 
It comes as Coleen herself admitted she doesn't feel like she deserved to win. 
During a chat with host Emma, she said: "Don’t make me cry I’ve done so much crying on this show. I’m traumatised. 
"I’ve never won anything in my life on my own ever. 
"If I put my hand on my heart I didn’t deserve to win it as I have been boring."
